Class PortRange

java.lang.Object
com.github.jh3nd3rs0n.jargyle.common.net.PortRange
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<Port>
public final class PortRange extends Object implements Iterable<Port>
A range of Port values between the provided minimum Port value and the maximum Port value (inclusive). A PortRange can also be one Port value.

    • of

      public static PortRange of(Port minPrt, Port maxPrt)
      Returns a PortRange of the provided minimum Port value and the maximum Port value. An IllegalArgumentException is thrown if the provided minimum Port value is greater than the maximum Port value.
      Parameters:
      minPrt - the provided minimum Port value
      maxPrt - the provided maximum Port value
      Returns:
      a PortRange of the provided minimum Port value and the maximum Port value

    • newInstanceFrom

      public static PortRange newInstanceFrom(String s)
      Returns a new PortRange from the provided String. The provided String must be a port number followed by a hyphen followed by another port number equal to or greater than the first port number. An IllegalArgumentException is thrown if the provided String is not valid.
      Parameters:
      s - the provided String
      Returns:
      a new PortRange from the provided String

    • toString

      public String toString()
      Returns the String representation of this PortRange. If the minimum Port value and the maximum Port value are the same, then the String representation is the String representation of the minimum Port value. If the minimum Port value and the maximum Port value are different, the String representation is the String representation of the minimum Port value followed by a hyphen followed by the String representation of the maximum Port value.
      Overrides:
      toString in class Object
      Returns:
